title: Pasig City Hall
description: The Pasig City Hall is located at Caruncho Avenue. Pasigueños go here to avail of the local government’s administrative services.
subject: city hall;

title: Pasig Cathedral
description: The Immaculate Conception Cathedral, or more commonly known as the Pasig Cathedral, is one of the oldest structures in Pasig. Catholic Pasigueños may go here to express their worship.
subject: church;

title: Plaza Rizal
description: Through the Plaza Rizal, Pasigueños also have a place for recreation. The open space coupled with the luscious greenery can serve as the right place to be with family and friends.
subject: plaza;park

title: Pasig Mega Market
description: A few walks from City Hall is the Pasig City Mega Market — popularly known as Pasig Palengke. The market is huge and contains a variety of food that Pasigueños can choose from.
subject: public market;

title: Rizal High School
description: Dubbed as the 2nd largest high school in the Guiness Book of World Record, the school has also become an iconic landmark for this accomplishment.
subject: school;
location: Dr. Sixto Antonio Ave., Pasig City

title: PhilSports Complex
creator: Mark Demayo
description: Another place for recreation is the PhilSports Complex. It was opened in 1985 and has a 10,000 person capacity.
subject: sports;

title: Pasig Revolving Tower
creator: patrickroque01
description: The Pasig Revolving Tower is a tourist attraction that can be found in the city. The 12-storey building was once called “Mutya ng Pasig”.
subject: building;

title: Pasig Rainforest Park (RAVE)
creator: UNTV News and Rescue
description: Another place that Pasigueños can go to for leisure is the Pasig Rainforest Park. It also has a mini-zoo that you can explore.
subject: park;

title: Estancia
creator: Ortigas Malls
description: The Estancia Mall has a variety of restaurants and other services that visitors can explore. The Capitol Commons Park is also within the vicinity, perfect for jogs and picnics.
subject: mall;
